<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class is a wrapper to associative container MapT&lt;KeyT, ValueT&gt; using</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the hash value of the original key as the new key. This greatly improves the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><Highlight kind="comment">/// performance of insert and query operations especially when hash values of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><Highlight kind="comment">/// keys are available a priori, and reduces memory usage if KeyT has a large</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="comment">/// size.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">/// All keys with the same hash value are considered equivalent (i.e. hash</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// collision is silently ignored). Given such feature this class should only be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// used where it does not affect compilation correctness, for example, when</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// loading a sample profile. The original key is not stored, so if the user</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// needs to preserve it, it should be stored in the mapped type.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Assuming the hashing algorithm is uniform, we use the formula</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1 - Permute(n, k) / n ^ k where n is the universe size and k is number of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// elements chosen at random to calculate the probability of collision. With</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1,000,000 entries the probability is negligible:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1 - (2^64)!/((2^64-1000000)!&#42;(2^64)^1000000) ~= 3&#42;10^-8.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birthday&#95;problem</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param MapT The underlying associative container type.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param KeyT The original key type, which requires the implementation of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">///   llvm::hash&#95;value(KeyT).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param ValueT The original mapped type, which has the same requirement as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">///   the underlying container.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param MapTArgs Additional template parameters passed to the underlying</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">///   container.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">...&gt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MapT,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> KeyT, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ValueT, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">... MapTArgs&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
